axi___05F0___05Fw___05Fvalid 0

1000
exit
```

compile:
```
verilator --cc --trace --exe --build --top SRAMAXI4 tb.cpp SoC.v
```

run:
```
./obj_dir/VSRAMAXI4 < tb
```

And examine simx.vcd. I was expecting that addr[0][31:0] is would be 00000000, then 44444444, and then 22222222. But verilator generates wrong c++ code:
```
    if (__VdlySet__SRAMAXI4__DOT__addr__v1) {
        vlSelfRef.SRAMAXI4__DOT__addr[0U] = 0x22222222U;
    }
    if (__VdlySet__SRAMAXI4__DOT__addr__v3) {
        vlSelfRef.SRAMAXI4__DOT__addr[0U] = 0x44444444U;
    }
    if (__VdlySet__SRAMAXI4__DOT__len__v0) {
        vlSelfRef.SRAMAXI4__DOT__len[0U] = __VdlyVal__SRAMAXI4__DOT__len__v0;
        vlSelfRef.SRAMAXI4__DOT__addr[0U] = 0x11111111U;
    }
    if (__VdlySet__SRAMAXI4__DOT__len__v1) {
        vlSelfRef.SRAMAXI4__DOT__len[0U] = 0xffU;
        vlSelfRef.SRAMAXI4__DOT__addr[0U] = 0x33333333U;
    }
```
and I get 00000000, then 33333333, and then 22222222.

PS. Icarus verilog works correctly with this SoC.v file.

